            "language_code": "en",
            "text": "Zoo Negara"
          }
        ]
      },
      "description": {
        "localized_texts": [
          {
            "language_code": "en",
            "text": "Zoo Negara Malaysia is managed by the Malaysian Zoological Society, a non-governmental organization established to create the first local zoo for Malaysians.Zoo Negara was officially opened on 14th November 1963 and has matured into a well-known zoo all around the world. We have a total of over 5137 specimen from 476 species of mammals, birds, reptiles, amphibians and fish.Zoo Negara covers 110 acres of land which is situated only 5km from the city of Kuala Lumpur.Over the years, the zoo has transformed itself to an open concept zoo with over 90% of its animals being kept in spacious exhibits with landscape befitting its nature."
          }
        ]
      },
      "rating": {
        "average_value": 4.3,
        "rating_count": 100
      },
      "product_features": [
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Also known as National Zoo of Malaysia, a popular attraction located in Ulu Klang, Gombak, Selangor."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Officially opened in 14 November 1963 and managed by Malaysian Zoological Society."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Wide Variety of Species: The zoo is home to over 400 species of mammals, birds, reptiles, amphibians, and fish."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Animal Shows: Sea lions, macaques, and macaws are part of a multi-animal show that is shown twice daily."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Mini Bee Museum: Located at the heart of Zoo Negara, this museum educates visitors about the many types of bees in the country."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_INCLUSION",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Zoo Negara, also known as the National Zoo of Malaysia, is a 110-acre zoological park in Selangor and home to over 5,000 animals from more than 450 species. The zoo features themed zones such as the African Savannah, Malaysian Rainforest, and Reptile Park, where visitors can see animals like tigers, lions, elephants, giraffes, and orangutans. Visitors can also enjoy animal shows, feeding activities, and interactive experiences, while learning about the zoo’s conservation and endangered species breeding programmes."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Accessibility: Wheelchair ramps and designated accessible pathways are available for most animal enclosures."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Restriction: Children under 12 years old must be accompanied by an adult at all times."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Restriction: For safety reasons, touching or feeding the animals is strictly prohibited.Feeding areas for specific animals, but only with zoo staff supervision."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Restriction: Bringing outside food and drinks into the zoo is not allowed and Pets of any kind are not allowed inside the zoo."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_INCLUSION",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "What’s included: One day admission to Zoo Negara which include Giant Panda Conservation Centre"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
